Sea Snake Young are found in the Miscellania and Etceteria Dungeon, which can be entered during and after the Royal Trouble quest.

They attack with ranged and are notably vulnerable to slashing weapons. As they are quite difficult to click, target cycle is useful.

This is one of the monsters that can drop the Giant snake spine required to complete the Fur 'n' Seek wishlist.

Update history[edit | edit source]

This information has been compiled as part of the update history project. Some updates may not be included – see here for how to help out!
  • patch 23 October 2017 (Update):
    • The walk animations for sea snake hatchlings and sea snake young have been updated and smoothed out.
  • patch 17 November 2009 (Update):
    • Fixed a problem with sea snakes and poison attacks.
  • update 22 May 2006 (Update):
    • Added to game.

Trivia[edit | edit source]

  • The examine information is a reference to a popular web cartoon, Badgers, by the English animation team Weebl's Stuff.
